"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-sports-2024-7-25-paris-olympics-2024-opening-ceremony-all-you-need-to-know\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 will make history as the first Olympic Summer Games to hold the opening ceremony outside a stadium.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.244774719137935e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save  Share  What:opening ceremony, Paris Olympics 2024When:7:30pm (17:30 GMT) on FridayHow to follow:Al Jazeera will havelive commentary and photos of the opening ceremonyas well as the build-up with what to expect.\", \"from\": 112, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 186, \"end\": 189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0933616652188363e-22, \"text\": \"GMT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\"}, {\"begin\": 214, \"end\": 224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999991379585559, \"rank\": 8.620411543563939e-07, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics 2024 will be officially launched on Friday with an opening ceremony in the French capital that will buck the trend of all the games that have come before it.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.989547817742788, \"rank\": 0.010081156060865954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's a breakdown of what we know ahead of what promises to be the latest in a long line of spectacularly staged curtain raisers at the Summer Olympics:  For the first time in the event's history, the opening ceremony will not be staged inside an Olympic stadium.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the Parisian spectacle will be staged on the city's main river, the Seine.\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 850, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5497942034474478e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The nature of the opening ceremony and the precise details remain under wraps, but organisers have promised a show like no other and said it will be \\\"daring and joyful\\\".\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A secret that was impossible to keep was that the Paris Olympic Stadium would not be included in the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators were told they would instead be required to line the banks of the Seine.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1225, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5497942034474478e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dozens of boats will carry thousands of athletes and performers on a 6km (3.7-mile) floating parade by river through the heart of the French capital.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1367, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.989547817742788, \"rank\": 0.010081156060865954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The extravaganza will depart from the Austerlitz Bridge, sail by Notre-Dame de Paris Cathedral and arrive near the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1422, \"end\": 1439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Austerlitz Bridge\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along the way, it will pass under bridges and gateways, including the Pont des Arts and Pont Neuf, while taking in many of the city's most famous landmarks.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1584, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont des Arts\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_des_Arts\"}, {\"begin\": 1602, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7832608629670382e-49, \"text\": \"Pont Neuf\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have promised \\\"there will not be a single riverbank or bridge that will not be filled with music, dance or performance\\\", adding that they will take advantage of the historic monuments, the riverbanks, the sky and water.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The artists who will perform throughout the event have been kept secret although the run time is expected to be four hours.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been widespread media reports that famous performers like Celine Dion and Lady Gaga are involved in the opening ceremony - but these reports have not been confirmed by the organisers.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2097, \"end\": 2108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.24104995353623e-37, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of the opening ceremony, painted the picture, however, by suggesting the show will be \\\"a large fresco\\\" celebrating Paris, France and the games and will interweave a parade of athletes, artistic performances and elements of protocol.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2224, \"end\": 2230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.8057032465528977, \"rank\": 0.22162968089388688, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}, {\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4735882206370026e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2382, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999798760819784, \"rank\": 1.578445417473057e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sitting on the banks of the Seine will be more than 100 heads of state and government while more than 300,000 spectators are also expected to line the river.\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2522, \"end\": 2527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5497942034474478e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of those, 104,000 will have to buy tickets while it is estimated a further 222,000 will get free invitations.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That number does not include those who will find ways to access free vantage points along the way.\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Organising Committee said about 10,500 athletes will take part in the opening ceremony and 80 giant screens along the route will offer intimate close-ups of the athletes and artists.\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 3059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.244774719137935e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among one of the more high-profile flag bearer announcements this week, it was revealed on Monday that basketball iconLeBron Jameswill be one of the athletes to carry the flag for Team USA at the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3096, \"end\": 3107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Standard-bearer\", \"score\": 0.9999999999463398, \"rank\": 3.6756554517962417e-11, \"text\": \"flag bearer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Standard-bearer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Standard-bearer\"}, {\"begin\": 3241, \"end\": 3249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999886313, \"rank\": 1.1293982241388624e-11, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French have left nothing to chance when it comes to security for the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3280, \"end\": 3286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.989547817742788, \"rank\": 0.010081156060865954, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Friday's event alone, there will be 45,000 police dispatched to ensure the ceremony's security.\", \"from\": 3368, \"to\": 3467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Special intervention forces along with snipers deployed on top of buildings will also be on duty, and the former have been on duty in plain sight in the days leading up to the ceremony.\", \"from\": 3469, \"to\": 3654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An anti-drone system will also be in place to prevent any aerial threats.\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The immediate vicinity of the riverbank has been shut off since July 18 with local residents required to carry permits on a QR code to get to their homes.\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators similarly will be required to use the same system to reach their viewing positions.\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The transportation system will also be restricted in the areas surrounding the Seine with cars allowed in only with special exceptions and metro stations shut down close to the river.\", \"from\": 3981, \"to\": 4164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4060, \"end\": 4065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5497942034474478e-23, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most bridges will also be closed while planes will be prevented from flying over Paris - unless they are part of the ceremony.\", \"from\": 4166, \"to\": 4292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4247, \"end\": 4252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4735882206370026e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France is already at its highest-level security alert with wars in both Gaza and Ukraine and security concerns at home.\", \"from\": 4294, \"to\": 4413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4294, \"end\": 4300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999798760819784, \"rank\": 1.578445417473057e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4366, \"end\": 4370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.6788593718276615, \"rank\": 0.4730591363977145, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 4375, \"end\": 4382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.999962680171577, \"rank\": 2.9923705425463382e-05, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although there is concern about attacks and other threats to the games as a whole, officials have said there were no specific threats to Friday's ceremony.\", \"from\": 4415, \"to\": 4570, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Given the extent of the security in place, a lone attacker is considered to be the main potential risk across the games, according to briefings by officials in recent months.\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Potential petty crime has been identified as a concern as have possible protests by environmental activists, the far right and far left, and the pro-Palestinian movement.\", \"from\": 4747, \"to\": 4917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A man suspected of planning an attack in the name of ISIL (ISIS) at the Saint-Etienne football stadium during the Olympics was arrested in May while a right-wing sympathiser was arrested this month in eastern France on suspicion of plotting attacks.\", \"from\": 4919, \"to\": 5168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4972, \"end\": 4976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.750922165965174e-13, \"text\": \"ISIL\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 4978, \"end\": 4982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.960333260726672e-27, \"text\": \"ISIS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_State\"}, {\"begin\": 5128, \"end\": 5134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999798760819784, \"rank\": 1.578445417473057e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are backup plans in place should specific concerns arise.\", \"from\": 5170, \"to\": 5233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They would either see the ceremony limited to the Trocadero Square near the Eiffel Tower or the Stade de France, which is serving as the Olympic Stadium.\", \"from\": 5234, \"to\": 5387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can follow the action on Al Jazeera's dedicatedParis 2024 Olympics tournament pagewith all the news and features, as well as event build-up and LIVE text commentary on selected football, basketball, tennis and boxing fixtures.\", \"from\": 5391, \"to\": 5621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5420, \"end\": 5430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999991379585559, \"rank\": 8.620411543563939e-07, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay informed with real-time updates from Paris 2024 with our Olympicsevents calendar,medal tableandresultspages.\", \"from\": 5622, \"to\": 5735, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5664, \"end\": 5674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.244774719137935e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 5755, \"to\": 5781, \"entities\": []}]}"